             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am a pawn-broker, I live with Mr. Caites in the Strand; on the 4th of July, the prisoner Redman pledged this shirt with me.</p>
               <p>(Deposed by the prosecutor.)</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="178709120015"></xptr>ROBERT PAYNE sworn.</p>
               <p>I am a pawn-broker, I live at Mr. Brown's in the Strand; the prisoner, (Redman) pledged these stockings with us in the month of June last; I lent him 1 s. on them.</p>
               <p>(Deposed to by the prosecutor.)</p>
               <p>The prisoners had nothing to say in their Defence.</p>
               <p>The prisoner Upon called two witnesses, who gave him a good character.</p>
               <p>The prisoner Kernon called three witnesses, who gave him a good character.</p>
               <p>The prisoner Redman called four witnesses, who all gave him a good character.</p>
